{"author":"Iso Tester","data":{"body":"Root cause (proven, joe-debug): NOT a signing-on-BLOCK code defect. plan_review/__init__.py:172-189 signs ONLY when verdict=='PASS'; on BLOCK the else-branch emits signature={signed:False, reason:'BLOCK'} — the object is ALWAYS present (non-null) but .signed is False. The claim gate (attest.py:claim_gate_check) verifies a real HMAC signature EVENT on the ticket via signing.verify_signature; sign_manifest is never called on BLOCK, so no event is written and the gate denies. Verified no other path (drift_refresh, orchestrator:543) signs on non-PASS. The reporter's 'signed=True' came from external batch tooling doing a PRESENCE/truthiness check on the always-present signature object instead of reading signature.signed. => Real bug is contract/docs clarity, not behavior. Fix: document the exact signature contract in docs/plan-review-gate.md + add a regression test pinning BLOCK->signed:False (no HMAC event, claim gate denies) and PASS->signed:True."},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"COMMENT","timestamp":1782779371366405001,"uuid":"05a1671a-1513-40c3-a75b-95d062d9191b"}